title: Guitar Songs
layout: layout
---

<p class="lead">This is a collection of songs for guitar meet ups to learn and play. They all use <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jJxRjWtwmEE">standard tuning</a> (E A D G B E).</p>

<p>Playlists of these songs are available on <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL0qpO5Cy9JamE_h3OEeNWm01ZfYyZFoyq">YouTube</a> and <a href="https://open.spotify.com/user/spilth/playlist/1NaTfvTr9vGRuLPFZ5vPPz">Spotify</a> but you'll need <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Guitar-Capos/b?ie=UTF8&node=486413011">a capo</a> to play along with some of them. During the meetups we'll play without a capo since not everybody owns one.</p>

<table class="table table-striped">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Title</th>
      <th>Artist</th>
      <th>Listen</th>
      <th>Chords</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <% data.guitar_songs.sort_by(&:title).each do |song| %>
    <tr>
      <td>
        <%= song.title %>
      </td>
      <td><%= song.artist %></td>
      <td>
        <% if song.spotify %>
          <%= link_to '<i class="fa fa-spotify" aria-hidden="true"></i>', song.spotify %>
        <% end %>
        <% if song.youtube %>
          <%= link_to '<i class="fa fa-youtube-play" aria-hidden="true"></i>', song.youtube %>
        <% end %>
      </td>
      <td>
        <% if song.chords %>
          <%= link_to "Chords", song.chords %>
        <% end %>
      </td>
    </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>
